author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: High-school football | City League roundup: Interception return lifts Marion-Franklin over Briggs
text:
Marion-Franklin 40, Briggs 17:   Allan McMichael-Roberts’ 19-yard interception return for a TD broke open a close game as Marion-Franklin (5-3, 4-1) defeated host Briggs (3-5, 1-4) in the City South.  
Briggs closed to within 20-17 in the third quarter when AJ Houchins scored on a 3-yard run, his second of the game. But Marion-Franklin pulled away, thanks to McMichael-Roberts’ play and two late TD runs by Anthony Hodnett and Derrione Leeper.  
Leeper finished with 165 rushing yards and two TDs. Houchins rushed for 166 yards for Briggs.  

Beechcroft 37, Centennial 6:  Rodell Rahmann caught three passes from Kyle Barrett, all for touchdowns, for 118 yards and Beechcroft (5-2, 4-0) cruised to a City League North win over visiting Centennial (2-6, 0-4). 

West 36, South 14:   Timothy Hufford scored two TDs, and West (4-4, 2-3) rushed for 336 yards en route to a win over visiting South (1-7, 1-4) in the City South. Byron White rushed for 175 yards on 21 carries and caught two passes for 55 yards for West. Demetrius Brown completed eight of 15 passes for 112 yards and a TD. Devjuawan Robinson rushed for 175 yards on 16 carries and scored on a 30-yard run for South.  

Walnut Ridge 68, Africentric 0:   Nine players scored touchdowns for Walnut Ridge (5-3, 4-1), which routed visiting Africentric (2-6, 0-5) in the City South. Malik Harrison scored twice for the Scots with runs of 63 and 54 yards. Brailon Hunter returned a fumble 20 yards for a score.
